2007-2008 to 2016-2017.","false","Biography information for Ms Angela Eagle","Wallasey","Ms Angela Eagle","128188"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843751","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>As one of its founding signatories, the UK strongly supports the international community's commitment to the Convention on the Prohibition of the Use, Stockpiling, Production and Transfer of Anti-Personnel Mines and on their Destruction (known as the Ottawa Convention). As well as working to meet our own convention-based commitments to clear our sovereign territory in the Falkland Islands of anti-personnel mines, the UK is committed to the global efforts to tackle the scourge of anti-personnel mines through our international mine action programmes. As a demonstration of the UK's commitment, the Secretary of State for the Department for International Development announced on 4 April 2017 that the UK would triple its spending on mine action in developing countries, taking UK expenditure to £100million over the three years to March 2020. The UK also regularly encourages states who have not signed the Convention to do so, most recently fully supporting Austria, as the outgoing President of the Convention, in urging all non-States Parties to join without delay, as well as encouraging signatory states to fulfil their obligations.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843751/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T17:31:35.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843751/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843751/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-19","Ottawa Convention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to support the international community's commitment to the Ottawa Mine Ban Treaty.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham P Jones","128189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843752","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-02-27","<p>The Ministry of Defence does not hold this information.</p><p>The UK was a founding signatory of the Ottawa Convention banning land mines and a number of UK organisations such as Mines Advisory Group (MAG) and the Halo Trust are at the forefront of global efforts to make the world mine-free.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843752/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T14:36:35.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843752/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843752/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-19","Land Mines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the number of live land mines laid by the British Army that are present in former war zones.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham P Jones","128190"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843753","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-02-27","<p>The UK is not providing training of any kind to the security forces of the Government of Yemen.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843753/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T14:35:39.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843753/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843753/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-19","Yemen: Land Mines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department is taking to train the security forces of the Yemini Government in landmine disarmament.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham P Jones","128191"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843754","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-02-27","<p>The Ministry of Defence does not undertake its own estimates of the number of landmines in Yemen.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843754/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T14:37:21.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843754/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843754/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-19","Yemen: Land Mines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate his Department has made of the number of landmines in Yemen.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham P Jones","128192"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843755","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-02-26","<p>This Government is a world leader in tackling plastic waste, not only banning microbeads, but also taking 9 billion plastic bags out of circulation with our 5p carrier bag charge.</p><p> </p><p>On 11 January we published our 25 Year Environment Plan that stated our ambition to eliminate all avoidable plastic waste by 2042 and, in particular, the waste from single-use plastics. The steps we will be taking to do this include exploring the introduction of plastic-free aisles by retailers; exploring how we can develop our producer responsibility schemes to give producers more incentives to design more resource efficient products; and extending the carrier bag charge to small retailers.</p><p> </p><p>In the 25 Year Environment Plan the Government also announced a plan to remove all consumer single use plastics from the central government estate offices. Defra Group are carrying out a full analysis of single use plastic through our supply chain and setting a requirement that new catering services exclude all consumer single use plastics. We work closely with other government departments and their agencies through the Greening Government Commitments to reduce their impacts on the environment.</p><p> </p><p>In autumn 2017 an independent working group set up under the Litter Strategy for England held a call for evidence on measures to reduce littering of drinks containers and promote recycling. This included seeking evidence on the costs, benefits and impacts of deposit return schemes. Ministers are now considering the working group’s report.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843755/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-26T17:52:32.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843755/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843755/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-02-19","Plastics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether his Department has a target for the reduction of single use plastics.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","128193"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843756","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-02-23","<p>Defra does not hold specific data on the volume of plastic waste from recycling facilities in Hertfordshire that was landfilled, incinerated, sent to energy recovery or exported. This is because data is not structured specifically around material streams or facilities and regions in this way.</p><p> </p><p>Under separate Producer Responsibility Obligations for packaging, where plastic packaging accounts for around 60% of total plastics arising’s in 2014, there are no accredited plastic reprocessors or accredited plastic exporters situated in Hertfordshire.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843756/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-23T17:02:53.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843756/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843756/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-02-19","Plastics: Hertfordshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what information his Departments holds on the volume of plastic waste from the recycling facilities in Hertfordshire that has been sent to (a) landfill, (b) incineration, (c) energy recovery and (d) exported abroad.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","128194"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843757","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-27","<p>Decisions on funding and access to social care support services for people with HIV are made by local authorities. The need for HIV social care support has changed since the early days of the epidemic when people were dying in large numbers. Data from Public Health England shows that someone diagnosed promptly and aged under 58 in 2016 has the same life expectancy as any other citizen. Therefore the need for social support has reduced.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843757/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T15:16:02.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843757/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843757/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","HIV Infection: Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what plans his Department has to increase funding for HIV support services.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","128195"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843758","Home Office","false","2018-02-22","<p>The Home Office collects information on crimes in which a knife or sharp instrument was used. However, this is not broken down to the type of instrument used, nor does it provide information on whether a member of the public was injured.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843758/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T16:05:19.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843758/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843758/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-19","Syringes: Injuries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what records her Department holds on the number of incidents in each of the last five years in which a member of the public has been injured by a used needle.","false","Biography information for Mr Simon Clarke","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Mr Simon Clarke","128196"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843759","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-22","<p>The Department does not anticipate any effect on take-up of other housing benefits as a result of this change. Claimants will be eligible for exactly the same level of financial support as they receive now. Loans will not be recovered until the property is sold and then only to the extent that there is sufficient equity available.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843759/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T12:20:21.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843759/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843759/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-19","Support for Mortgage Interest","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment her Department has made of the potential effect of changing support for mortgage interest to a loan on the take-up of other housing benefits.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","128197"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843760","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-22","<p>The Department does not hold the data requested.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843760/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T11:43:44.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843760/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843760/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-19","Support for Mortgage Interest","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate her Department has made of the number of people who participate in the Home Ownership for people with Long-term Disabilities scheme who will be affected by the replacement of support for mortgage interest with a loan.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","128198"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843761","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-22","<p>The table below provides forecasts of the caseload for Support for Mortgage Interest (SMI) in 2017/18 by region.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Region</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Estimated SMI caseload (000s)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North East</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North West</p></td><td><p>16</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Yorkshire and Humberside</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>East Midlands</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>West Midlands</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>East</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London</p></td><td><p>12</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South East</p></td><td><p>12</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South West</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wales</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Scotland</p></td><td><p>12</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>110</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em> </em></p><p>Notes:</p><ul><li>Figures have been rounded to the nearest 1,000 cases and may not sum due to rounding.</li></ul><ul><li>DWP does not hold a single source of data on SMI claims to analyse. Analysis of regional SMI caseloads are based on DWP’s Quarterly Statistical Extract (QSE) data. QSE is a quarterly 5 per cent sample of Jobseeker’s Allowance (JSA), Income Support (IS) and Pension Credit (PC) claimants. Quality assured data at regional level is not available for ESA or UC claimants receiving SMI. In the absence of data the regional breakdown of ESA claimants has been assumed to be the same as the JSA, IS and PC caseload. Less than 1% of SMI claimants are estimated to claim UC in 2017/18.</li><li>Estimates use QSE data over four quarters up to May 2017 and are calibrated to the 2017/18 SMI caseload forecast published in the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/benefit-expenditure-and-caseload-tables-2017" target="_blank">Benefit Expenditure and Caseload Tables</a>.</li></ul><p> </p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843761/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T17:10:14.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843761/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843761/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-19","Support for Mortgage Interest","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if she will set out the number of claimants of support for mortgage interest in each region of England and Wales in the most recent 12-month period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","128199"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843762","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-22","<p>The Department does not hold the data requested.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843762/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T11:56:13.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843762/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843762/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-19","Support for Mortgage Interest","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many households in receipt of support for mortgage interest had a property repossessed in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","128200"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843763","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-02-22","<p>The assessment that the Secretary of State made on 7 November 2017, when the he announced that he was 'minded-to' implement the locally-led proposal for improving local government in Dorset, was that this proposal if implemented is likely to improve local government across the area.</p><p>I am now assessing the proposal afresh, carefully considering all of the representations I have received, and I intend to announce my final decision shortly with the aim of achieving the best result for the people of Dorset.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak","128202","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843763/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T14:11:20.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843763/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843763/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-02-19","Local Government: Dorset","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what assessment his Department has made of the merits of the proposed future Dorset local government review.","false","Biography information for Wera Hobhouse","Bath","Wera Hobhouse","128201"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843764","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-02-22","<p>The assessment that the Secretary of State made on 7 November 2017, when the he announced that he was 'minded-to' implement the locally-led proposal for improving local government in Dorset, was that this proposal if implemented is likely to improve local government across the area.</p><p>I am now assessing the proposal afresh, carefully considering all of the representations I have received, and I intend to announce my final decision shortly with the aim of achieving the best result for the people of Dorset.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak","128201","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843764/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T14:11:20.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843764/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843764/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-02-19","Local Government: Dorset","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what assessment his Department has made of the merits of the Future Dorset Proposal.","false","Biography information for Wera Hobhouse","Bath","Wera Hobhouse","128202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843765","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-02-22","<p>The three proposals for merging district councils, which the Department has been considering over the last 12 months, have been assessed as delivering annual savings ranging from £0.8 to £3.1 million with pay back periods for covering one off transition costs from 1 to 3 years.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843765/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T14:11:47.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843765/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843765/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-02-19","Local Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what estimate his Department has made of the average cost to the public purse of local authority mergers in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Wera Hobhouse","Bath","Wera Hobhouse","128203"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843766","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-02-22","<p>Our policy is to consider against the criteria the Secretary of State announced on 7 November 2017, any proposal for merging district councils when requested. It is for the councils making such a proposal to decide how to demonstrate the level of local support for it.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843766/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T14:09:02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843766/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843766/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-02-19","Local Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, if he will make it his policy that local referenda take place in advance of local authority mergers.","false","Biography information for Wera Hobhouse","Bath","Wera Hobhouse","128204"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843767","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-02-22","<p>We deeply value the contribution of all 150,000 EU citizens working in our health and care sector, they are vital to ensuring the effective delivery of services. Safeguarding the rights of EU citizens who are currently living in the UK, and ensuring reciprocal protections for UK nationals living in the EU was our first priority for negotiations.</p><p>It is a commitment we have delivered. The agreement reached in December will secure the status rights of EU nationals working in our health and care system, including doctors, meaning they will be able to stay and enjoy broadly the same rights and benefits as they do now.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843767/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T17:13:42.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843767/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843767/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-02-19","Doctors: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what discussions he has had with his counterpart in the EU on retaining non-UK EU doctors after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","128205"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843768","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-27","<p>The Department continues to monitor and analyse overall staffing levels across the National Health Service and we are working across Government to ensure there will continue to be sufficient staff to deliver the high quality services on which patients rely following the United Kingdom’s exit from the European Union.</p><p> </p><p>This includes working with the Home Office to secure a future migration system which ensures that we can meet future and growing demand, not just for doctors but for all those who work across the health and care system.</p><p> </p><p>The latest figures from NHS Digital show that there were over 3,200 more EU nationals working in the NHS in September 2017 than before the referendum result.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has also confirmed the biggest ever expansion in the number of doctors training places of 1,500 by September 2019 to make sure the NHS has the staff it needs to provide a first class service for patients.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843768/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T16:48:55.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843768/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843768/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Doctors: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what plans he has to support the recruitment by the NHS of doctors from the EU after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","128206"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843769","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-27","<p>The Government’s Childhood Obesity Plan launched in August 2016 will help children and families to recognise and make healthier choices and be more active. Key measures in the plan include the soft drinks industry levy, the sugar reduction and wider reformulation programme and helping children to enjoy an hour of physical activity every day.</p><p>Public Health England's social marketing campaign, Change4Life aims to help families and children in England to eat well and move more. The campaign has had high levels of engagement across Yorkshire and the Humber using multiple platforms including roadshows in Hull, North Lincolnshire, North East Lincolnshire, Leeds and Bradford. Through this campaign the Government, the National Health Service, local authorities, businesses, charities, schools, families and community leaders could all play a part in improving children’s diets and activity levels. ‘Our Healthy Year’ resources for Reception and Year 6 primary school teachers and school nursing teams to integrate engaging curriculum-linked activities on following a healthy diet and being more active in the daily school routine have been distributed to primary schools across Yorkshire and the Humber and are available to download for free from the Change4Life School Zone website, available to view here:</p><p><a href="https://campaignresources.phe.gov.uk/schools" target="_blank">https://campaignresources.phe.gov.uk/schools</a></p><p>The Healthy Child Programme is the key universal public health service, delivered by health visitors, for improving the health and wellbeing of children. Its goals are to identify and treat problems early, help parents to care well for their children, change health behaviours and protect against preventable diseases. The programme is evidence-based and aims to prevent problems in child health and development and contribute to a reduction in health inequalities.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843769/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T15:33:19.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843769/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843769/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Obesity: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps the Government is taking to increase awareness of the dangers of obesity in children and young people in Yorkshire and the Humber.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","128207"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843770","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-02-27","<p>I refer the Hon Member to the answer to Question UIN 124260 on 29 January 2018.</p><p>In addition to the measures set out in that answer, we specifically encourage use of modern and innovative methods of construction through the Affordable Homes Programme 2016-21. This includes offsite construction and we expect to fund an increasing number of bids using either partial or fully offsite or innovative methods of construction within the Programme.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843770/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T17:43:56.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843770/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843770/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-02-19","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what plans his Department has to encourage the use of quick build, flat pack homes for social and affordable housing.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","128208"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843771","Home Office","false","2018-02-23","<p>The Home Office closely monitors Accommodation Providers to ensure that they adhere to contractual requirements to consider individual characteristics, including gender, when allocating appropriate accommodation. Services users are not accommodated in mixed-sex dispersal accommodation unless part of a same family unit. Those service users who are accommodated in initial accommodation are provided with same sex rooms or blocks. Information on the gender mix of individual properties is not held in a reportable format and the requested information could therefore only be provided at disproportionate cost by examination of individual property records.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843771/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-23T15:19:29.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843771/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843771/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-19","Asylum: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many female asylum-seekers are housed in mixed-sex accommodation.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","128209"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843772","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-27","<p>The Government is committed to making the transport system accessible to all users, including small children. The draft Accessibility Action Plan, published for consultation last year, set out a number of steps we will be taking across transport modes.</p><p> </p><p>The Equality Act 2010 makes provision for operators of public transport services to make reasonable adjustments to accommodate passengers who share protected characteristics, which include age and pregnancy &amp; maternity.</p><p> </p><p>Mainline trains must comply with standards for vehicle design to make them more accessible to persons of reduced mobility, which includes babies and children. Currently 78% of the mainline rail fleet meet these standards, and work is underway to improve this. In addition, 75% of rail journeys are covered by step-free stations, while stations are also covered by design standards that take into account persons of reduced mobility.</p><p> </p><p>Buses, taxis and private hire vehicles provide an invaluable service for many people, and it is essential that they meet the needs of those wishing to use them. Some bus operators have invested in vehicles with additional space for buggies and prams, beyond the minimum accessibility requirements, and we encourage taxi licensing authorities to ensure that vehicle fleets work for a range of passengers.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843772/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T16:38:41.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843772/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843772/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-19","Transport: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to improve the accessibility of railways, buses, coaches and trams for small children.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","128210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843773","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-02-27","<p>The Government is committed to ensuring that victims of crime have access to a broad range of support services, to help them cope with and, as far as possible, recover from the effects of crime.</p><p> </p><p>We are spending about £96m this year to fund critical support services for victims of crime, of which, £68m has been allocated to Police and Crime Commissioners to locally commission emotional and practical support services for victims of crime.</p><p> </p><p>In 2017/18 we have allocated: -</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>PCC Area</p></td><td><p>Grant to PCC</p></td><td><p>Grant Funding to Rape Support Centres</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North Yorkshire</p></td><td><p>£948,483</p></td><td><p>£43,812</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South Yorkshire</p></td><td><p>£1,838,150</p></td><td><p>£281,648</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>West Yorkshire</p></td><td><p>£2,674,679</p></td><td><p>£240,966</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Humberside</p></td><td><p>£1,120,595</p></td><td><p>£143,624</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>To help meet increased demand we provided rape support centres with an in year 4% uplift in core funding.</p><p> </p><p>The PCC for South Yorkshire received an uplift of £226,750 on their 2017/18 grant as a contribution towards the Rotherham Fusion bid (Operation Stovewood), for the provision of additional Independent Sexual Violence Advisor support services.</p><p> </p><p>The PCC for Humberside received an uplift of £36,208 on their 2017/18 grant funding in recognition of the increased demand for local rape support services.</p><p> </p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843773/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T16:35:43.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843773/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843773/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-02-19","Crime: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps his Department is taking to increase support for victims of crime in Yorkshire and the Humber.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","128211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843774","Home Office","false","2018-02-22","<p>It is important that all crimes including minor crimes are reported to the police so that they can be investigated and, where appropriate, the offenders charged and prosecuted in the courts.</p><p>It is for Chief Constables and Police and Crime Commissioners, as operational leaders and elected local representatives, to decide how best to deploy policing resources to prevent, tackle, and respond to crimes being committed.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843774/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T17:30:38.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843774/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843774/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-19","Crime Prevention: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps her Department is taking to deter people from committing minor offences in Yorkshire and the Humber.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","128212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843775","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>The Government position regarding the status of the Tibet Autonomous Region remains consistent. We regard it as part of the People's Republic of China (PRC). We regularly urge China to respect all fundamental rights across the PRC, including in Tibet, in line with both its own constitution and the international frameworks to which it is a party.</p><p>We pay close attention to the human rights and wider situation in Tibet and the Government regularly raises the issue with the Chinese authorities. We raised our concerns directly with the Chinese authorities at the last round of the UK/China Human Rights Dialogue which took place in Beijing on 27 June 2017. We also set out our human rights concerns about China, and specifically in the Tibet Autonomous Region, in the Foreign and Commonwealth Office annual report on Human Rights and Democracy, which was issued on 20 July 2017.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843775/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T15:50:21.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843775/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843775/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-19","Tibet: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his counterpart in the Chinese Government on (a) the status of and (b) human rights in Tibet.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","128213"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843776","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-02-26","<p>The Phalanx Close-In Weapon System and light gun mounts, (which I have taken to refer to mini gun and general purpose machine gun mountings) on board HMS OCEAN will remain in the Ministry of Defence inventory to be allocated to Royal Navy ships as determined by operational requirements.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843776/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-26T16:26:41.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843776/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843776/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-19","HMS Ocean","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether (a) Phalanx CIWS and (b) light gun mounts on board HMS OCEAN will be donated to Queen Elizabeth class carriers or other Royal Navy vessels once that vessel is decommissioned.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","128214"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843777","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-22","<p>NHS England publishes allocations for each clinical commissioning group (CCG) on its website. Per capita allocations for core CCG services for London CCGs in 2017-18 are listed on page 12, column 19 of the document that can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/ccg-allocations.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/ccg-allocations.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>It should be noted that the figures for 2017/18 do not include any adjustments that may have been agreed since the time of publication.</p><p> </p><p>Revised allocations for core CCG services for 2018-19 were published in February 2018, and are accessible via the link below. Per capita allocations for London CCGs can be found on page 3, column 11.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Revised-CCG-allocations-2018-19-1.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Revised-CCG-allocations-2018-19-1.pdf</a></p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843777/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T16:33:58.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843777/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843777/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Clinical Commissioning Groups: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how much funding was allocated to each clinical commissioning group area in London per head of population in 2017-18; what funding is proposed to be so allocated in 2018-19; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","128215"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843778","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-02-27","<p>It is policy that all prisoners are issued with a plain nylon bag to carry his or her property upon final release.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843778/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T17:32:51.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843778/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843778/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-02-19","Prisoners' Release","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, which prisons provide prisoners with their possessions in a holdall on release.","false","Biography information for Iain Stewart","Milton Keynes South","Iain Stewart","128216"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843779","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>The UK is committed to the full implementation of UN Human Rights Council Resolution 34/1, under which Sri Lanka committed to implement a range of measures to provide for human rights, truth-seeking, reconciliation, and devolution of political powers following the end of its civil war. I encouraged Foreign Minister Marapana to continue to make progress on these commitments when I met him in Colombo, in October 2017. Our High Commission in Sri Lanka regularly travel to the North and East (as did I to Jaffna during that visit) and meet with local groups, and where we have specific human rights concerns we raise these with the Sri Lankan government.</p><p>This year the UK will continue to encourage progress on human rights issues, including modern slavery, gender inequality, and reform of discriminatory laws.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843779/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T15:54:18.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843779/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843779/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-19","Sri Lanka: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the human rights record of the Government of Sri Lanka.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","128217"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843780","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>The UK is closely monitoring delivery of the commitments made by the Government of Sri Lanka under UN Human Rights Council Resolution 34/1 (which rolls over commitments under 30/1), in collaboration with the UN, international partners, Government of Sri Lanka and civil society.</p><p>During my visit to Colombo and Jaffna in October 2017 I discussed the importance of the Sri Lankan government meeting its obligations. Among these were establishing transitional justice mechanisms, including a credible accountability process for those most responsible for violations and abuses during Sri Lanka's civil war and the return of military held civilian land, particularly in the predominantly Tamil north and east.</p><p>The UK continues to support the Government of Sri Lanka in its efforts to promote reconciliation and human rights. And we anticipate making further representations on the publication this march of the UN Interim Report on the implementation of Resolution 34/1. The UK is also providing Sri Lanka with £6.6 million of Conflict, Stability and Security Fund funding over three years, to include support for police reform and training, reconciliation and peace building, and demining in the north of the country.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843780/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T16:04:24.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843780/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843780/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-19","Sri Lanka: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps the Government is taking to help ensure that the Sri Lankan Government observes UN Human Rights Council Resolution 30/1 on promoting reconciliation, accountability and human rights in Sri Lanka.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","128218"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843781","Department for International Trade","false","2018-02-27","<p>I refer the Hon. Member for Lewisham, Deptford to the answer I gave to my Hon. Friend for Welwyn Hatfield on 23 January 2018, UIN: 124349</p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843781/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T17:55:47.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843781/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843781/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-02-19","Arms Trade: Sri Lanka","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what steps the Government is taking to ensure that arms sold to the Government of Sri Lanka are not used to perpetrate human rights violations in that country.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","128219"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843782","Cabinet Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>UK public procurement policy is to award contracts on the basis of value for money, which means the optimum combination of cost and quality over the lifetime of the project. It is for individual contracting authorities to ensure that they do not accept bids that are not viable.</p><p>The Public Contracts Regulations 2015 sets out the way in which Contracting Authorities shall require bidders to explain the price or costs proposed in a tender, where it appears to be abnormally low in relation to the requirement. Where the Contracting Authority considers the explanation and evidence to be unsatisfactory, it can reject the tender.</p><p>In addition, the Public Contracts Regulations 2015 allow contracting authorities to impose requirements ensuring that economic operators possess the necessary economic and financial capacity to perform the contract, and a supplier’s past performance is taken into account.</p><p>Where appropriate, Open Book Contract Management techniques can be used to closely monitor contract delivery, and to understand bidders' cost models and margins.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843782/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T16:46:35.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843782/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843782/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-19","Government Departments: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps he is taking to prevent unsustainable bids being accepted in Government procurement.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128220"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843783","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-22","<p>The NCSC continues to investigate all ongoing incidents providing tailored advice where required. This will be reported in the Annual review, expected in October 2018.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843783/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-03-22T09:28:28.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843783/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843783/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-19","Electronic Government: Hacking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which Government websites were affected by the recent hack which used websites to mine cryptocurrency.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128221"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843784","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-22","<p>The finalisation of the evaluation has proved complex, and we are still in the process of agreeing the final draft. There is a standard 12 week clearance and formatting period from the time the final draft is agreed to publication. We will make the publication date available once it has been confirmed.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843784/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T12:17:37.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843784/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843784/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-19","Social Security Benefits: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when her Department plans to publish the evaluation of the yellow card sanctions pilot in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","128222"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843785","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-02-27","<p>The Department does not have an estimate of the number of people affected. The incident is being investigated by technical experts at the National Cyber Security Centre (NCSC.) The NCSC judges that any effect would have been temporary.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843785/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T17:12:09.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843785/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843785/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-02-19","Hacking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate her Department has made of the number of people affected by the cyber attack reported by the BBC on 11 February 2018 in which hackers took control of other people's computers to mine cryptocurrency.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128223"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843786","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-02-27","<p>The National Cyber Security Centre is not aware of anything that would indicate that any personal data was stolen as a result of this incident.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843786/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T16:37:31.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843786/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843786/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-02-19","Hacking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what information the Government holds on the amount of personal data which was stolen as a result of the recent BrowseAloud hack.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128224"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843787","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-22","<p>NHS England issued advice to general practitioners (GPs) and community pharmacists on 5 February 2018 on which influenza vaccines should be ordered for the adult seasonal flu programme (eligible individuals aged 18 years and over) in 2018/19. This advice was sent to ensure that GPs and community pharmacists order the most clinically effective vaccines for the coming season.</p><p> </p><p>A copy of the letter is attached.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843787/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T14:14:11.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843787/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843787/answer","Vaccine ordering for 2018-19 influenza season GPpharm 05022018.pdf","Vaccine ordering for 2018-19 influenza season GPpharm 05022018.pdf","PQ128225 attached document","PQ128225 attached document","17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Influenza: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, if he will publish the correspondence between his Department,  Public Health England and NHS England on the type of vaccine that GPs have been advised to order for winter 2018-19.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","128225"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843788","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-02-22","<p>The information requested is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843788/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T16:48:56.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843788/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843788/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-02-19","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, which external recruitment agencies are used by his Department's non-departmental public bodies.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","128226"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843789","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-22","<p>There has been no study undertaken on the estimate of the number of people who have contracted flu in winter 2017-18 after receiving the trivalent vaccine instead of the quadrivalent vaccine.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843789/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T14:17:41.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843789/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843789/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Influenza: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what estimate his Department has made of the number of people who have contracted flu in winter 2017-18 after receiving the trivalent vaccine instead of the quadrivalent vaccine.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","128227"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843790","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-22","<p>NHS England has contracting arrangements with five NHS trusts which have provided adult extracorporeal membrane oxygenation (ECMO) treatment in England in each year since 2013. These are:</p><p>- Guy’s and St Thomas’ NHS Foundation Trust;</p><p>- Papworth Hospital NHS Foundation Trust;</p><p>- Royal Brompton and Harefield NHS Foundation Trust;</p><p>- University Hospital of South Manchester NHS Foundation Trust; and</p><p>- University Hospitals of Leicester NHS Trust.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England also has contracting arrangements with five NHS trusts which have provided paediatric ECMO treatment in England in each year since 2013. These are outlined below:</p><p>- University Hospitals of Leicester NHS Trust;</p><p>- Newcastle upon Tyne NHS Foundation Trust;</p><p>- Great Ormond Street Hospital Foundation Trust;</p><p>- Birmingham Women's and Children's NHS Foundation Trust; and</p><p>- Alder Hey Children’s NHS Foundation Trust.</p><p> </p><p>Data prior to 2013 is not held centrally.</p><p> </p><p>Published standard operating procedure on the NHS England website sets out the actions that NHS England and NHS trusts take to manage surges in demand for ECMO services. This is available via the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/commissioning/ccs/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/commissioning/ccs/</a></p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","128291","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843790/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T16:36:51.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843790/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843790/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Respiratory System: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, if he will set out (a) how many and (b) which hospitals in England have provided extracorporeal membrane oxygenation treatment, in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","128228"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843791","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-22","<p>The Department’s non-departmental public bodies (NDPBs) have provided the attached information.</p><p> </p><p>NDPBs are able to procure staff from the Crown Commercial Services (CCS) Non-Medical Non Clinical framework for permanent and temporary workers and the CCS Contingent Labour One framework for temporary workers.</p><p> </p><p>The two frameworks are not mandated for NDPBs to use, and are able to use alternative routes to procure staff.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843791/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T14:39:22.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843791/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843791/answer","NDPBs - recruitment agencies table.docx","NDPBs - recruitment agencies table.docx","PQ128229 attached document","PQ128229 attached document","17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Department of Health and Social Care: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, which external recruitment agencies are used by his Department's non-departmental public bodies.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","128229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843792","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-02-22","<p>The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy does not hold centrally any information on the external recruitment agencies used by its non-departmental public bodies.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843792/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T16:15:22.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843792/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843792/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-19","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, which external recruitment agencies are used by his Department's non-departmental public bodies.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","128230"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843793","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-14","<p>The Cabinet Office has a framework of 6 executive agencies is available for senior recruitment across all Government departments and Arms Length Bodies. The agencies are Russell Reynolds, Odgers Berndtson, Gatenby Sanderson, Veredus, Carbon and Moloney Search. Arms Length Bodies are also able to contract external recruitment agencies through the Dynamic Purchasing System.</p><p> </p><p>The information is available here: <a href="http://ccs-agreements.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/contracts/ps-2016-ps-services" target="_blank">http://ccs-agreements.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/contracts/ps-2016-ps-services</a></p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843793/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-03-14T15:03:09.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843793/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843793/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-19","Cabinet Office: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which external recruitment agencies are used by his Department's non-departmental public bodies.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","128231"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843794","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>The Prime Minister tasked the Foreign Secretary to establish and chair an Interministerial Group to oversee and coordinate the Government's response to hurricane recovery in the region. That group was last updated on recovery efforts at the beginning of this month and will next meet in March.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843794/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T12:43:19.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843794/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843794/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-19","Caribbean: Humanitarian Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions has he had with Cabinet colleagues on ensuring continued humanitarian assistance to those Overseas Territories in the Caribbean which were damaged by hurricanes in 2017.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","128232"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843795","Home Office","false","2018-02-26","<p>The Government recognises the impact that retail crime has on businesses. The British Retail Consortium, for example, estimated that the direct financial cost of crime to the UK retail industry was £660 million in 2015-16. We do not yet have data for the estimated cost of retail crime to the UK retail industry in 2017.</p><p>We work closely with the retail sector through the National Retail Crime Steering Group, which brings together representatives from industry, Government and the Police. This includes the British Retail Consortium and the Association of Convenience Stores to understand better the crime issues that affect the sector and how we can best work together to prevent and respond to these crimes.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843795/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-26T18:26:39.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843795/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843795/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-19","Retail Trade: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate her Department has made of the cost of retail crime to the UK economy in 2017; and what steps her Department is taking to tackle retail crime.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","128233"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843796","Home Office","false","2018-02-22","<p>Tackling knife crime is a priority for the Government. Our work to tackle knife crime is centred on four key strands – working with the police on operations and enforcement, work on the legislative framework, work with retailers on responsible sales, and early intervention and prevention. All this work is designed to protect the public wherever they are and wherever they work.</p><p> </p><p>All acts of violence and abuse against retail staff are serious matters whenever and wherever they occur. All such incidents should be reported to the police and taken seriously, investigated and, where appropriate, the perpetrators taken through the courts and met with tough sentences.</p><p>At the national level, we are working with the police and the retail sector to identify what more can be done to prevent and respond to violence and abuse against retail staff, as part of the work of the National Retail Crime Steering Group. The Steering Group is jointly chaired by the Home Office and the British Retail Consortium.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843796/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T16:20:34.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843796/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843796/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-19","Retail Trade: Crimes of Violence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps her Department is taking to reduce incidences of knife crime against shop workers.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","128234"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843797","Women and Equalities","false","2018-02-28","<p>The Equality Act 2010 provides a number of protections for disabled people in situations including employment, education and the provision of goods and services.</p><p>Political parties are within the scope of the Act. They must make reasonable adjustments for disabled people to ensure that they are not put at a significant disadvantage in accessing membership, and associated rights and benefits when compared to people without disabilities.</p><p>This duty means that political parties are required to provide reasonable additional support to disabled candidates to ensure, so far as possible, that they have the same access as non-disabled candidates.</p><p>The Equality and Human Rights Commission has recently launched a guide for political parties on their responsibilities under Equality Act 2010, which provides further information on their legal responsibilities. A link is below:</p><p><a href="https://www.equalityhumanrights.com/en/publication-download/equality-act-2010-guide-political-parties" target="_blank">https://www.equalityhumanrights.com/en/publication-download/equality-act-2010-guide-political-parties</a></p><p>The Local Government Association has guidance on how disabled people can become councillors, a link to which is below:</p><p><a href="https://www.local.gov.uk/sites/default/files/documents/be-councillor-guide-disab-e85.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.local.gov.uk/sites/default/files/documents/be-councillor-guide-disab-e85.pdf</a></p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843797/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-28T12:56:45.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843797/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843797/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2018-02-19","Access to Elected Office for Disabled People Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, pursuant to the Answer of 6 February to Question 125982 with reference to the Equality and Human Rights Commission's recommendation that the Government reopen the Access to Elected Office Fund, what support she provides for people with disabilities who are seeking elected office.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","128235"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843798","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-22","<p>Performance and trends in the number and type of cases cleared by the Independent Case Examiner’s Office are reviewed and reported in the Independent Case Examiner’s Annual Report which is published on gov.uk.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843798/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T17:03:25.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843798/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843798/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-19","Independent Case Examiner","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment she has made of trends in the level of cases examined and cleared by the Independent Case Examiner between 2010-11 and 2017-18 and what steps she is taking to improve the performance of that service.","false","Biography information for Marion Fellows","Motherwell and Wishaw","Marion Fellows","128236"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843799","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-27","<p>Copies of correspondence from the Government of the Republic of Ireland dated 28 November and 7 December 2016 and from my Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State to the Government of the Republic of Ireland dated 13 January 2017, on Orkambi are attached.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843799/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T15:17:27.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843799/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843799/answer","Doc1.pdf ; Doc2.pdf ; Doc3.pdf","Doc1.pdf ; Doc2.pdf ; Doc3.pdf","PQ128237 attached document ; PQ128237 attached document ; PQ128237 attached document","PQ128237 attached document ; PQ128237 attached document ; PQ128237 attached document","17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Orkambi: Republic of Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the Answer of 19 January 2018 to Question 122358, on Orkambi: Republic of Ireland, if he will place copies of that correspondence in the Library.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","128237"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843800","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-27","<p>NHS England has advised that the correspondence requested is commercially sensitive and therefore it would not be appropriate to release this information.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843800/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T15:17:07.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843800/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843800/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Orkambi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, with reference to the Government's response to e-petition 209455, on making Orkambi available on the NHS for people with cystic fibrosis, if he will place copies of the correspondence between NHS England and Vertex in the Library.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","128238"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843801","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-02-22","<p>Proposals in the draft Domestic Gas and Electricity (Tariff Cap) Bill will only apply to the implementation of a cap on standard variable and default tariffs. Energy companies would be able to challenge Ofgem’s decision on the setting of the cap by way of judicial review. It does not remove an existing right of appeal.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843801/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T15:57:13.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843801/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843801/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-19","Energy: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the removal of appeal rights for energy companies to an independent body, as indicated in the draft Domestic Gas and Electricity (Tariff Cap) Bill, will also apply to National Grid’s RIIO price controls.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","128239"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843802","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-02-22","<p>The impact assessment for the Domestic Gas and Electricity (Tariff Cap) Bill will be reviewed by the Regulatory Policy Committee.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843802/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T16:00:35.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843802/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843802/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-19","Energy: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether the Regulatory Policy Committee will scrutinise the draft Domestic Gas and Electricity (Tariff Cap) Bill; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","128240"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843803","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-02-22","<p>The draft Bill would place a new duty on Ofgem to implement a cap on standard variable and default tariffs. It does not remove an existing right of appeal. Energy companies would be able to challenge Ofgem’s decision on the setting of the cap by way of judicial review, and the Government believes that a Court is capable of considering these matters.</p><p> </p><p>Government Bills are drafted by the Office of the Parliamentary Counsel based on instructions from Government lawyers. We are content that the provisions set out in the draft Bill are compliant with the law.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843803/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T15:58:06.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843803/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843803/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-19","Energy: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether his Department sought legal advice on the removal of appeal rights to an independent body as contained in the draft Domestic Gas and Electricity (Tariff Cap) Bill; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","128241"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843804","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-22","<p>The Department does not hold the data requested. The data needed to make robust estimates of the number of recipients of Support for Mortgage Interest (SMI) at geographies smaller than Government Office Region is not available to Departmental analysts.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843804/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T11:52:59.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843804/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843804/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-19","Support for Mortgage Interest: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in each parliamentary constituency in Scotland receive support for mortgage interest; and how many of those people also receive (a) employment support allowance, (b) personal independence payments and (c) jobseeker’s allowance.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","128242"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843805","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-02-27","<p>The Competition and Markets Authority (CMA) is the independent non-ministerial department responsible for investigating market-wide competition issues in the UK. The CMA has not recently conducted a study or investigation into the funeral industry but regularly reviews what market issues should be included within its work portfolio, in line with its published prioritisation principles.</p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843805/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T13:58:15.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843805/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843805/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-19","Funerals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what recent assessment he has made of the level of competition in the funeral industry.","false","Biography information for Matt Western","Warwick and Leamington","Matt Western","128243"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843806","Department for Education","false","2018-02-27","<p>The public sector pay cap is no longer in place and we have adopted a more flexible approach to public sector pay. The Department's remit letter to the School Teachers’ Review Body (STRB) states that the STRB should utilise this flexibility to target the next pay award to promote recruitment and retention.</p><p> </p><p>The fundamental changes to teachers’ pay that have been introduced over the last four years, following the STRB’s recommendations, have given greater autonomy to schools to decide how to reward their staff. This increased flexibility helps schools to attract and retain the best teachers and to target any school-level recruitment and retention problems they may have, including addressing teacher shortages in specific subjects.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843806/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T16:49:39.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843806/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843806/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-02-19","Schools: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of the public sector pay cap on the recruitment and retention of staff in schools in (a) England, b) London and (c) Lewisham Deptford constituency.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","128244"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843807","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-02-27","<p>The Competition and Markets Authority (CMA) is the independent non-ministerial department responsible for investigating market-wide competition issues in the UK. The CMA has not recently conducted a study or investigation into the funeral industry but regularly reviews what market issues should be included within its work portfolio, in line with its published prioritisation principles.</p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843807/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T13:59:00.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843807/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843807/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-19","Funerals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the extent of exploitative practices in the funeral industry.","false","Biography information for Matt Western","Warwick and Leamington","Matt Western","128245"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843808","Women and Equalities","false","2018-02-23","<p>I am pleased to see that women’s impressive achievements in sport are gaining increasing recognition, and am delighted that three women have won medals for Team GB at the Winter Olympics so far. The Minister for Women and Equalities has not attended any women’s sporting events since her recent appointment but hopes to do so in the future.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843808/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-23T16:00:44.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843808/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843808/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2018-02-19","Females: Sports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, which women's sporting events she has attended since becoming Minister for Women and Equalities.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Sir Mark Hendrick","128246"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843809","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-02-27","<p>The proportion of under 18 recruits that attended Army Foundation College (Harrogate) in each of the last three financial years is shown below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>2016-17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>75%</p></td><td><p>78%</p></td><td><p>79%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>These figures are single service estimates and are not official statistics produced by Defence Statistics.</p><p> </p><p><strong><br> </strong></p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843809/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T14:32:15.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843809/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843809/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-19","Army: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of recruits under 18 years of age attended the Army Foundation College in Harrogate in each of the last three years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","128247"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843810","Department for Education","false","2018-02-27","<p>Wakefield City Academies Trust is taking a trust-wide perspective of its finances, which many academy trusts do. The department is working to ensure all 21 academies transfer to incoming trusts in a way that secures the financial future for each school and the education of their pupils. All 21 academies will transfer to their new trusts with a balanced budget position, enabling incoming trusts to give each school a fresh start. To support this, the department is providing appropriate funding to the incoming trusts to improve pupil outcomes. The academies will be moving to a much more financially secure environment, and will be receiving excellent support from trusts with proven track records.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","128249 ; 128250","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843810/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T16:19:17.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843810/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843810/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-02-19","Wakefield City Academies Trust","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what information his Department holds on the amount of funding removed from individual school budgets by the Wakefield City Academy Trust.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","128248"
