"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843812","Department for Education","false","2018-02-27","<p>Wakefield City Academies Trust is taking a trust-wide perspective of its finances, which many academy trusts do. The department is working to ensure all 21 academies transfer to incoming trusts in a way that secures the financial future for each school and the education of their pupils. All 21 academies will transfer to their new trusts with a balanced budget position, enabling incoming trusts to give each school a fresh start. To support this, the department is providing appropriate funding to the incoming trusts to improve pupil outcomes. The academies will be moving to a much more financially secure environment, and will be receiving excellent support from trusts with proven track records.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","128248 ; 128249","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843812/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T16:19:17.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843812/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843812/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-02-19","Wakefield City Academies Trust","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether funding removed from individual school budgets by Wakefield City Academy Trust will be reimbursed.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","128250"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843813","Cabinet Office","false","2018-02-26","<p>The independent Advisory Committee on Business Appointments (ACOBA) is responsible for advising Government and former Ministers on the application of the Business Appointment Rules. It publishes its advice online, ensuring that its consideration and any conditions imposed are publicly available, to encourage effective scrutiny and accountability for former ministers and senior civil servants.</p><p>ACOBA will also make its views public when applications are received retrospectively, in order to draw attention to an individual’s failure to seek the Committee’s advice in advance of taking up a role<em>.</em></p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington","128252","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843813/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-26T16:53:51.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843813/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843813/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-19","Former Ministers: Business Interests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what mechanisms are in place to monitor compliance by former Ministers of conditions set by the Advisory Committee on Business Appointments for their appointments.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128251"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843814","Cabinet Office","false","2018-02-26","<p>The independent Advisory Committee on Business Appointments (ACOBA) is responsible for advising Government and former Ministers on the application of the Business Appointment Rules. It publishes its advice online, ensuring that its consideration and any conditions imposed are publicly available, to encourage effective scrutiny and accountability for former ministers and senior civil servants.</p><p>ACOBA will also make its views public when applications are received retrospectively, in order to draw attention to an individual’s failure to seek the Committee’s advice in advance of taking up a role<em>.</em></p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington","128251","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843814/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-26T16:53:51.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843814/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843814/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-19","Senior Civil Servants: Business Interests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what mechanisms are in place to monitor compliance by former senior civil servants of conditions set by the Advisory Committee on Business Appointments for their appointments.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843815","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-26","<p>There is no legal basis for moving people onto Universal Credit in areas where roll out is yet to take place, and so there is no guidance to staff on giving advice to claimants in these circumstances.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843815/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-26T16:44:10.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843815/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843815/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-19","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if she will place her Department’s guidance to JobCentre Plus staff on advising benefit claimants whether to claim for universal credit in areas where its roll-out has not yet been made compulsory in the Library.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham P Jones","128253"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843816","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-22","<p>The Civil Aviation Authority (CAA) – the industry regulator – has responsibility for managing and leading meetings on aerotoxic syndrome. The Department for Transport (DfT) last met with unions and individuals to discuss aerotoxic syndrome prior to the 2011 publication of DfT commissioned Cranfield University research into cabin air quality.</p><p> </p><p>These research findings were submitted to the Committee on Toxicology (COT) in 2012 who published a position paper on cabin air in 2013. There was no evidence for pollutants on board aircraft occurring at levels exceeding the health and safety standards and guidelines outlined in Chapter 5 of Cranfield University’s “Aircraft Cabin Air Sampling Study; Part 1 of the Final Report”.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843816/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T18:00:31.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843816/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843816/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-19","Aircraft: Air Conditioning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when (a) he or (b) Officials of his Department last met with unions or individuals to discuss aerotoxic syndrome.","false","Biography information for Rosie Duffield","Canterbury","Rosie Duffield","128254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843817","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-26","<p>Data is not available that distinguishes these cases from other new claims to Universal Credit.</p><p> </p><p>Currently, claimants moving from existing benefits to Universal Credit will only do so because they will have had a change in their circumstances that would previously, under the legacy system, have triggered a new claim to benefits or tax credits. Entitlement would have been calculated based on the rules of their new benefit, taking in to account their new circumstances.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843817/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-26T16:56:52.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843817/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843817/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-19","Universal Credit: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what information her Department holds on the number of (a) universal credit claimants who have lost benefit income as a result of benefit migration and (b) single parents who have lost benefit income as a result of universal credit in areas of Lancashire where its roll-out has not yet been made compulsory.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham P Jones","128255"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843818","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-02-22","<p>English Housing Survey data is publicly available and can be downloaded from the UK Data Service: <a href="http://discover.ukdataservice.ac.uk/series/?sn=200010" target="_blank">http://discover.ukdataservice.ac.uk/series/?sn=200010</a></p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843818/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T14:06:24.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843818/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843818/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-02-19","Owner Occupation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 12 February 2018 to Question 127028, on owner occupation, whether his Department (a) holds or (b) is able to place in the Library the information requested.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","128256"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843819","Cabinet Office","false","2018-02-26","<p>This information is publicly available in the Advisory Committee on Business Appointments’ annual reports. The reports can be found here <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=advisory-committee-on-business-appointments&amp;publication_type=corporate-reports" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=advisory-committee-on-business-appointments&amp;publication_type=corporate-reports</a></p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843819/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-26T16:51:02.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843819/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843819/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-19","Business Appointments Advisory Committee","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much money was spent by the Advisory Committee on Business Appointments (a) on staffing and (b) in total in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128257"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843820","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-02-22","<p>HMCTS Probate provides additional support to all customers, including vulnerable people and people with learning difficulties who are engaging in the Probate Process by way of advice on completing the application by experienced staff. Staff will provide guidance through published information on all aspects of the process that the applicant will have to go through. They will support customers attending Probate Offices and will address concerns raised by telephone or by email. It is not the role of HMCTS staff to provide legal advice.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843820/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T17:36:57.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843820/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843820/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-02-19","Probate: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what support his Department provides, in addition to the probate and inheritance tax helpline, for vulnerable people and people with learning difficulties who are engaging with the probate process.","false","Biography information for Rosie Duffield","Canterbury","Rosie Duffield","128258"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843821","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-27","<p>NHS England confirms that Diabetes Transformation Funding of £1.75 million has been awarded to the Kent and Medway Sustainability and Transformation Partnership. The first quarter’s payment was made on 30 June 2017, the second quarter’s payment was made on 29 September, the third quarter’s payment was made on 29 December and the fourth quarter’s payment will be made on 28 February 2018.</p><p> </p><p>The Sustainability and Transformation Partnership was successful in obtaining diabetes transformation funding to make improvements in respect of the following treatment targets:</p><p>- Increasing uptake of diabetes structured education with the aim of a reduced risk of diabetes-related complications; and</p><p>- Increasing availability of multidisciplinary footcare teams with the aim of reduced rates of amputations for people with diabetes.</p><p> </p><p>We would expect local commissioners to assess the impact of these improvements in the coming years.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","128263 ; 128266","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843821/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T16:53:04.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843821/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843821/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Diabetes: Kent","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, on what date £1.75 million in funding from the Diabetes Transformation Fund was transferred to the Kent and Medway Sustainability and Transformation Partnership.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","128259"
