"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843832","Home Office","false","2018-03-12","<p>The question is a matter for the College of Policing to answer, but I can confirm that while the College does not provide standalone advice or consultancy services, it does provide bespoke training packages to international partners.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843832/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-03-12T18:38:06.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843832/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843832/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-19","College of Policing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, to what countries the College of Policing and its predecessor body has provided (a) training, (b) advice and (c) consultancy services in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","128270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843833","Department for International Trade","false","2018-02-22","<p>The Government is considering its position on these issues. Measures to transpose these requirements do not need to be in place until 14 December 2019.</p><p> </p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843833/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T17:59:57.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843833/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843833/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-02-19","Arms Trade: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to the Answer of 5 February 2018 to Question 126452, what steps the Government is taking to comply with section three of the EU Firearms Directive in respect of (a) establishing a system for the regulation of the activities of dealers and brokers and (b) checking the private and professional integrity and the relevant abilities of the dealer or broker.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","128271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843834","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-02-22","<p>​The UK helped secure the landmark Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) and we meet the UN's 0.7% gross national income target for Official Development Assistance (ODA). The Foreign and Commonwealth Office, as a leading ODA-spending department, is helping to advance the SDGs globally by contributing to the objectives of the UK Aid Strategy, particularly in the areas of peace and security, governance and economic development.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843834/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T17:29:06.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843834/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843834/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-19","Sustainable Development","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs what assessment his Department has made of the contribution of Official Development Assistance to the achievement of sustainable development goals.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","128272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843835","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-02-22","<p>​The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) remains committed to meeting the target for Official Development Assistance (ODA) Transparency laid down in the UK Aid Strategy, ie, to achieve a rating of Good or Very Good in the International Aid Transparency Index by 2020. We continue to make improvements to the way ODA expenditure is accounted for in our financial and programme management systems and processes. An independent audit by Publish What You Fund is underway and due to report on FCO ODA transparency in June 2018. The FCO will use the recommendations made in this review to make further improvements to its ODA transparency.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843835/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T17:30:46.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843835/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843835/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-19","Overseas Aid: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to increase the transparency of Official Development Assistance spending.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","128273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843836","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-02-22","<p>The UK keeps under consideration whether a new UN resolution would support progress towards a political settlement in Yemen. Given the lack of agreement between the parties at present we judge that the best opportunity for progress comes through the appointment of Martin Griffiths as the new UN Special Envoy for Yemen, which we welcomed. We encourage the parties to return to negotiations and participate constructively in the UN-led political process.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843836/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T17:58:26.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843836/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843836/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-02-19","Yemen: Peace Negotiations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the Government plans to table a resolution on Yemen in the UN Security Council.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","128274"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843837","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-23","<p>As of 20<sup>th</sup> February 2018, 45 complaints relating to women born in the 1950s and affected by changes in state pension, had been fully reviewed by the Independent Case Examiner’s Office.</p><p> </p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843837/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-23T16:26:38.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843837/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843837/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-19","State Retirement Pensions: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many complaints relating to women born in the 1950s and affected by changes in state pension age have been fully reviewed by the Independent Case Examiner's Office.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","128275"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843838","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-23","<p>As of 20<sup>th</sup> February 2018 there were 1,800 complaints from women born in the 1950s who are affected by changes in state pension age awaiting allocation to an investigation case manager.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843838/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-23T16:43:01.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843838/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843838/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-19","State Retirement Pensions: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many complaints relating to women born in the 1950s who are affected by changes in state pension age are awaiting allocation to an investigation case manager at the Independent Case Examiner's Office.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","128081"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843839","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-23","<p>As at 20 February 2018, the Independent Case Examiner’s Office were allocating dedicated Investigation Case Managers:</p><ul><li>Disability, Pensions, Working Age and Debt Management complaints that were accepted on or after 22 November 2016.</li><li>Provider complaints that were accepted on or after 24 November 2016</li><li>Child Maintenance Group complaints that were accepted on or after 31 January 2017</li><li>WASPI complaints that were accepted on or after 27 March 2017</li></ul>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843839/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-23T16:36:36.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843839/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843839/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-19","Independent Case Examiner","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, from what acceptance date the Independent Case Examiner's Office is allocating complaints to an investigation case manager.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","128276"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843840","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-23","<p>As at 20<sup>th</sup> February 2018 there were 523 Disability, Pensions, Working Age and Debt Management complaints (excluding those relating to changes in state pension retirement age) awaiting allocation to an Investigation Case Manager.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843840/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-23T16:39:21.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843840/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843840/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-19","Independent Case Examiner","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many disability, pensions, working age and debt management complaints are awaiting allocation to an investigation case manager at the Independent Case Examiner's Office.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","128277"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843841","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-23","<p>At 20<sup>th</sup> February 2018 there were 252 Child Maintenance Group Complaints awaiting allocation to an investigation case manager.</p><p><em></em></p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843841/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-23T16:45:09.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843841/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843841/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-19","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many Child Maintenance Group complaints are awaiting allocation to an investigation case manager at the Independent Case Examiner's Office.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","128086"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843842","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-23","<p>At 20<sup>th</sup> February 2018, there were 256 service provider complaints awaiting allocation to an investigation case manager.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843842/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-23T16:41:04.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843842/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843842/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-19","Independent Case Examiner","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many of her Department's service providers' complaints are awaiting allocation to an investigation case manager at the Independent Case Examiner's Office.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","128278"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843843","Scotland Office","false","2018-02-22","<p>I currently have no plans to visit a food bank in my capacity as Secretary of State for Scotland in March 2018.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843843/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T14:16:00.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843843/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843843/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-02-19","Scotland Office: Food Banks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, whether he plans to visit a food bank in March.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","128279"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843844","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-27","<p>The Government is concerned about the impact of long term use of prescription opioids. The Department has commissioned Public Health England to undertake an evidence review to better understand the scope of the problem of prescribed drug dependence.</p><p> </p><p>The review will bring together the best available evidence on prevalence and prescribing; the nature and likely causes of dependence or discontinuation syndrome among some people who continue to take these medicines; and effective prevention and treatment responses for each condition they are prescribed for.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843844/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T16:52:06.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843844/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843844/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Prescription Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps his Department is taking to reduce the number of people who overdose on prescription opioids.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","128090"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843845","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-02-27","<p>BEIS Ministers and officials meet stakeholders to discuss a range of issues.</p><p> </p><p>The Government published the draft Domestic Gas and Electricity (Tariff Cap) Bill on 12 October 2017 for pre-legislative scrutiny by the BEIS Committee, which the devolved administrations were able to respond to.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843845/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T17:07:01.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843845/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843845/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-19","Energy: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what discussions he has had with the devolved administrations on the draft Domestic Gas and Electricity (Tariff Cap) Bill.","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","128280"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843846","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-02-27","<p>The prepayment meter safeguard (price cap) tariff covers around 5 million households in Great Britain (around 4 million on pre-payment meters and around 1 million recipients of the Warm Home Discount). Ofgem estimated that the introduction of the cap saved an average PPM customer £60 a year, and even with the recent change the cap will remain £34 cheaper than the market average standard variable tariff.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843846/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T17:07:51.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843846/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843846/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-19","Energy: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what estimate his Department has made of the number of households in (a) Scotland, (b) England, (c) Wales and (d) Northern Ireland which will be affected by Ofgem’s decision to increase its price cap by £57 a year from April 2018.","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","128094"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843847","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-02-27","<p>The draft Bill proposes to require Ofgem to review and report on whether the conditions for effective competition are in place and to make a recommendation to the Secretary of State. This will inform the Secretary of State’s decision on whether the cap should remain in force. The first review and report would be in 2020 and each year, up to 2023, that the price cap remains in place.</p><p>In designing the methodology for setting the level of the price cap we would expect that Ofgem would need to consider how to take account of relevant changes in costs such as for wholesale energy.</p><p>The prepayment safeguard tariff was introduced by the Competition and Markets Authority (CMA) following its investigation into the energy markets. The methodology set by the CMA, and administered by Ofgem, to calculate the cap is based on wholesale costs, network costs, policy costs, operating costs, and costs specifically associated with prepayment meters.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843847/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T17:08:09.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843847/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843847/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-19","Energy: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the implications are for his legislative proposals on requiring Ofgem to review the price cap only once a year from 2020 of Ofgem’s decision to increase the level of its pre-payment meter price cap as a result of increasing wholesale costs.","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","128281"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843848","Department for Education","false","2018-02-22","<p>The Construction Industry Training Board (CITB) is proactively working with their established network of college partners to support all affected apprentices and other learners to complete their programmes. Additionally, they are utilising their existing employer contacts in the sector, in order to find and secure alternative employers for the apprentices to complete their frameworks or standards.</p><p>CITB has emailed 40,000 external contacts, the vast majority of whom are employers, encouraging them to take on Carillion apprentices and to highlight the incentives CITB have put in place to secure employment for affected learners.</p><p>The Education and Skills Funding Agency contacted all affected apprentices on 15 January 2018 to notify them of the situation and next steps. CITB confirmed that they contacted all learners on the 17 January 2018, via telephone, email and text message, to begin the transfer process, with a focus on minimising disruption to the learner and their learner journey.</p><p>CITB has established a dedicated helpline for apprentices seeking support and has also delivered a series of workshops for learners, which have taken place in the localities of the 11 Carillion Training Centres. These workshops provided advice on next steps and offer 1 to 1 support, as required. The timings and locations of these events were communicated to learners through telephone calls, email and a comprehensive social media campaign.</p><p>CITB has engaged directly with over 1,200 learners to date, has already secured new employment, with wages, for over 700 of the apprentices and is working progressively to find alternative employers for all those affected. At present, it has been agreed that all former Carillion apprentices will continue to be paid beyond 31 January, whilst alternative employers are being sought.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843848/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T17:03:13.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843848/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843848/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-02-19","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 19 January 2018 to Question 122931 on Carillion, of the 1,200 apprentices affected, how many of those apprentices (a) have been found alternative employers and (b) are in receipt of jobseeker’s allowance.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","128282"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843849","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-02-27","<p>In the Smart Systems and Flexibility Plan, published last July, the Government and Ofgem said that measures should be taken to limit the ownership and operation of electricity storage by distribution network operators. This is to prevent competitive activities being carried out by monopoly network operators, which would inhibit fair competition in the market. Ofgem subsequently consulted on limiting the ownership and operation of storage by distribution network operators in October last year, and we expect Ofgem to finalise their position in the coming months.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843849/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T17:00:22.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843849/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843849/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-19","Electricity: Storage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether he has made an assessment of the potential merits of re-classifying electricity storage vessels to enable distribution network operators to utilise such vessels without paying generation charges.","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","128098"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843850","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-02-27","<p>My right hon. Friend the Secretary of State launched the joint Government and Ofgem Smart Systems and Flexibility Plan in July 2017, in which we committed to 29 actions to facilitate the transition to a smarter, more flexible energy system. One of these actions was for network operators and industry to continue to improve network connection processes for electricity storage. As part of this commitment, the Energy Networks Association recently published a guidance document called ‘Information on Distribution Connection Options’ which aims to provide clarity on connections options, and is the first output of their work on this issue. We expect further guidance as their work continues, including greater transparency for storage operators on where best to connect. Several Distribution Network Operators have already published so-called ‘heat maps’ for this purpose, and we expect others to follow suit.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843850/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T16:59:28.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843850/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843850/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-19","Electricity: Storage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps his Department is taking to identify locations for potential electricity storage schemes that would best supplement the existing National Grid system; what steps his Department is taking to facilitate such installations; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","128283"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843851","Home Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>Guernsey have a central register of company beneficial ownership information.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843851/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T15:55:26.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843851/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843851/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-19","Companies: Guernsey","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Office, whether Guernsey has introduced a private register of beneficial ownership.","false","Biography information for Dame Margaret Hodge","Barking","Dame Margaret Hodge","128102"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843852","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-02-27","<p>Network charging, including balancing services use of system charges, is a matter for Ofgem as the independent regulator. Ofgem published a consultation on a Targeted Charging Review in March 2017, also setting out its views on network charges for storage. These views are that storage should not face demand residual charges at transmission and distribution level, and should not face two sets of balancing system charges. Industry has since brought forward code modification proposals, including one addressing balancing charges, and these are currently going through the industry codes modification process.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843852/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T17:01:49.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843852/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843852/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-19","Electricity: Storage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment his Department has made of the potential merits of exempting operators of electricity storage from balanced services use of system charges.","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","128284"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843853","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-22","<p>There are 70 extended or newly established community eating disorders services being developed across the country and recruitment to get the teams up to full capacity is well under way. This means at least 3,350 children and young people a year will receive swift, effective eating disorder treatment in the community — for many this will mean they will be treated earlier and no longer need to go into hospital. Further information is available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/2017/09/nhs-england-comments-on-ucl-and-national-childrens-bureau-report-on-young-peoples-depression/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/2017/09/nhs-england-comments-on-ucl-and-national-childrens-bureau-report-on-young-peoples-depression/</a></p><p>In Sussex, all seven clinical commissioning groups have commissioned a national eating disorder charity (BEAT) to raise awareness and training for professionals and to develop a sustainable parent/carer support network. A Family Eating Disorder Service has also been collaboratively commissioned which complies with the National Access and Waiting Time Standards for children’s eating disorder services.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843853/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T11:34:43.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843853/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843853/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Eating Disorders: Brighton","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what recent assessment he has made of the adequacy of eating disorder services for children and young people in Brighton and Hove.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","128105"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843854","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-02-27","<p>The Green Deal Framework remains in place and we are aware that various sources of private finance have continued to be utilised under the Framework. As such, the Green Deal was at no point ended and consequently will not be “re-launched”.</p><p> </p><p>We are, however, looking to improve and revitalise the Green Deal. My department published a Call for Evidence on the Green Deal Framework in October 2017. We are considering the responses and will consult on any proposals to reform the Green Deal in due course. Current participants in the Green Deal scheme must continue to adhere to all the requirements of the scheme that apply to them.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","128288","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843854/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T17:11:30.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843854/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843854/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-19","Green Deal Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether he plans to introduce a new code of practice for green deal providers and assessors in the relaunched green deal.","false","Biography information for Ged Killen","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Ged Killen","128285"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843855","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-02-27","<p>Green Deal Providers are just one of four key authorised participants involved in the Green Deal customer journey, each with different customer interactions. There are also differences in the requirements to become authorised participants. The criteria that they have to meet are set out in the Green Deal Framework (Disclosure, Acknowledgement, Redress etc.) Regulations 2012.</p><p> </p><p>Organisations are not required to have UKAS approval in order to become Green Deal Providers.</p><p> </p><p>It is not the Provider’s role to produce Green Deal reports (or “Green Deal Advice Reports”). This is the responsibility of the Green Deal Assessor. No Providers, therefore, have been refused the right to produce Green Deal reports.</p><p> </p><p>The table below sets out the number of organisations, by year, who have been registered as Green Deal Providers. These numbers do not take account of the numbers by year who have withdrawn from the scheme. The total number of currently-authorised Providers is 169.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>19</p></td><td><p>100</p></td><td><p>52</p></td><td><p>16</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Devizes","Claire Perry","128115 ; 128286","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843855/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T17:02:59.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843855/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843855/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-19","Green Deal Scheme: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of St