"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843902","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-27","<p>There are five privately managed prison contracts, all of which have provisions in place for palliative care. For those prisons where NHS England holds commissioning responsibility, they commission end of life and palliative care provision, support the prisons’ approach to the local authorities’ assessment and management of social care, and ensure that elderly patients are supported in accessing healthcare services.</p><p>NHS England has developed a ‘Dying Well in Custody Charter’, mirroring the community based Dying Well Charter, scheduled to be published this spring.</p><p>Information on receiving palliative care from Her Majesty’s Prison and Probation Service by age is not held centrally.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","128183 ; 128308","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843902/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T15:21:04.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843902/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843902/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Palliative Care: Prisoners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many prisoners aged over (a) 60, (b) 70 and (c) 80 receive palliative care from Her Majesty’s Prison and Probation Service.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","128309"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843903","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-16","<p>The Commission gathers information on the use of exceptions from departments annually. This is available at: <a href="http://civilservicecommission.independent.gov.uk/appointments-exception-scs-pay-band-2-2/" target="_blank">http://civilservicecommission.independent.gov.uk/appointments-exception-scs-pay-band-2-2/</a></p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843903/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-03-16T14:21:56.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843903/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843903/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-19","Civil Servants: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many exceptions to the legal requirements set out in the Civil Service Commission's Recruitment Principles there have been since 2010; and to which appointments those exceptions applied.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128185"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843904","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-26","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the statement made by myself, <a href="https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2018-01-30/debates/F35E85CB-FF67-467E-AD63-1C13EB1EC32B/PIPBackPayments" target="_blank">Official Report</a>, 30 January 2018, Column 703.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843904/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-26T12:24:04.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843904/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843904/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-19","Personal Independence Payment: Inverclyde","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in the Inverclyde constituency will have their personal independence payment claim reviewed by the Government.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","128310"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843905","HM Treasury","false","2018-02-22","<p>HM Revenue and Customs have procedures in place to ensure that any parent who experiences a technical issue when applying for their 30 hours code through the online service do not lose out.</p><p> </p><p>Honourable members are able contact HM Revenue &amp; Customs Tax Credits MP helpline in order to report issues and ask questions relating to the childcare service. The helpline is available from 9am-5pm, Monday to Friday.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","128313","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843905/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T15:22:54.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843905/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843905/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-19","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many parents or carers entitled to 30 hours free childcare have failed to receive a code from Childcare Services as a consequence of technical issues in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128311"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843906","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-21","<p>To date, the One Public Estate programme has supported the creation of at least 5,740 jobs. A yearly breakdown is shown below.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Jobs created</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>137</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>328</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>5,217</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017/18 (to date)</p></td><td><p>58</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>5,740</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Benefits reported by One Public Estate partnerships must also be accompanied by evidence. In addition to those which have been verified, partnerships have reported further job creation. As such, yearly totals can be expected to rise.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843906/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-03-21T13:00:10.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843906/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843906/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-19","One Public Estate Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate his Department has made of the number of new jobs created by the One Public Estate Programme in each year since 2013.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128312"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843907","HM Treasury","false","2018-02-22","<p>HM Revenue and Customs have procedures in place to ensure that any parent who experiences a technical issue when applying for their 30 hours code through the online service do not lose out.</p><p> </p><p>Honourable members are able contact HM Revenue &amp; Customs Tax Credits MP helpline in order to report issues and ask questions relating to the childcare service. The helpline is available from 9am-5pm, Monday to Friday.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","128311","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843907/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T15:22:54.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843907/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843907/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-19","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will establish an MP enquiry number for the Childcare Office to assist Members' constituents as a result of technical failures relating to the generation of codes for free childcare provision.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128313"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843908","Cabinet Office","true","2018-02-27","<p>The One Public Estate (OPE) programme is establishing a Pool of Experts to support local OPE partnerships to deliver property-based projects. At present, 23 experts have been accepted into the Pool, as set out below.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><ins class="ministerial"><strong>Specialism</strong></ins></p></td><td><p><ins class="ministerial"><strong>Experts</strong></ins></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><ins class="ministerial">Masterplanning</ins></p></td><td><p><ins class="ministerial">2</ins></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><ins class="ministerial">Feasibility and Options Appraisals</ins></p></td><td><p><ins class="ministerial">2</ins></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><ins class="ministerial">Surveying</ins> <ins class="ministerial"><em>(Building)</em></ins> <ins class="ministerial"><em>(Chartered)</em></ins> <ins class="ministerial"><em>(Quantity) </em></ins></p></td><td><p><ins class="ministerial">10</ins> <ins class="ministerial"><em>(8)</em></ins> <ins class="ministerial"><em>(2)</em></ins> <ins class="ministerial"><em>(0)</em></ins></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><ins class="ministerial">Project Management</ins></p></td><td><p><ins class="ministerial">9</ins></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><ins class="ministerial">Design</ins></p></td><td><p><ins class="ministerial">0</ins></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><ins class="ministerial">Procurement</ins></p></td><td><p><ins class="ministerial">0</ins></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><ins class="ministerial"><strong>Total (to date)</strong></ins></p></td><td><p><ins class="ministerial"><strong>23</strong></ins></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><ins class="ministerial"> </ins></p><p><ins class="ministerial">The programme’s selection process is still underway. In addition to the 23 appointed, a further 35 are going through the application process. Recruitment has been marketed externally and no experts are currently Civil Servants.</ins></p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843908/answer","Hertsmere","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843908/answer/previousversion/43708","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843908/answer/previousversion/43708","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843908/answer/previousversion/43708",,,"2018-02-27T17:39:32Z","2018-02-28T10:39:17.593Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843908/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843908/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-19","One Public Estate Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet, how many people are in the One Public Estate programme's Pool of Experts; from which parent teams in the Civil Service those people have come; and for each such team which of its members of the Pool of Experts have (a) master planning, (b) feasibility studies, (c) options appraisals, (d) surveyors, (e) design and (f) procurement expertise.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128314"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843909","Cabinet Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>Five projects were put forward for Sustainable Pilot Grant funding by One Public Estate partnerships in November 2017. As the programme was substantially over-subscribed, projects put forward for standard grants were also considered for pilot funding where they met the required criteria. As such, more than five Sustainable Pilot Grant awards have been offered. The programme is currently finalising these awards.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843909/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T16:32:47.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843909/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843909/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-19","One Public Estate Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many applications have been made for repayable grants by the One Public Estate programme pilot scheme.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128315"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843910","Department for Transport","false","2018-02-27","<p>The figures for the last three years are as follows:</p><p> </p><p>2016/17: £91m</p><p>2015/16: £75m</p><p>2014/15: £33m</p><p> </p><p>The figures above represent the sale proceeds less any costs associated with selling the property.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843910/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T11:44:18.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843910/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843910/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-02-19","Network Rail: Property","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, the value of property sold by Network Rail in each of the last three years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128316"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843911","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-23","<p>The One Public Estate programme partnered with the Ministry for Housing, Communities and Local Government in late 2017 to support the delivery of the Land Release Fund. As part of the joint programme’s expanded pre-selection criteria, we request that local authorities provide information on land released since 2015, beyond that recorded through One Public Estate projects. Successful Land Release Fund bids were announced on 16 February. The new requirement will form part of future quarterly monitoring.</p><p>The One Public Estate (OPE) programme currently holds data concerning land which has been released by local authorities in relation to One Public Estate projects. This allows the programme to quantify its contributions to releasing public sector land for new homes. This forms part of OPE’s core objectives to create economic growth and contribute to Government’s housing agenda. To provide as much available information as possible, the relevant programme data is set out below.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Land released for homes </strong> <strong>(housing units)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>792</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>92</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>599</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017/18</p></td><td><p>560</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2,043</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>This data is collected quarterly from OPE partnerships as part of the monitoring and reporting requirements of the programme.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843911/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-03-23T11:51:20.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843911/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843911/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-19","One Public Estate Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what data the One Public Estate programme holds on local authority land released since 2015 which has been collected through applications to that programme.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128317"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843912","Cabinet Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>The One Public Estate (OPE) programme has held six application rounds since the programme began in 2013. 210 applications have been received in total, including 122 applications made by groups of local authorities, and 88 by sole local authorities. It is important to note that whilst OPE partnerships are local authority-led, they comprise wider public sector partners, including central government departments. A yearly breakdown of applications is shown in the table below.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Sole Authority Applications</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Joint Applications</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>12</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>28</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>23</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>23</p></td><td><p>53</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017/18</p></td><td><p>19</p></td><td><p>42</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>88</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>122</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>One Public Estate carries out a rigorous assessment process against published criteria. Not all applications submitted were successful.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843912/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T17:55:46.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843912/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843912/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-19","One Public Estate Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many local authority applications to the One Public Estate programme were (a) joint applications and (b) applications by a sole local authority in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128318"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843913","Cabinet Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>One Public Estate does not typically collect the data requested. The information requested cannot be provided without incurring a disproportionate cost.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843913/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T17:51:52.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843913/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843913/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-19","One Public Estate Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many applications to the One Public Estate programme included (a) joint ventures, (b) land swaps and (c) development by small and medium-sized enterprises in each of the last five years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128319"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843914","Cabinet Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>One Public Estate does not typically collect the data requested regarding small and medium-sized enterprises. The information requested cannot be provided without incurring a disproportionate cost.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843914/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T16:34:40.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843914/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843914/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-19","One Public Estate Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many (a) applications and (b) successful applications to the One Public Estate programme include key projects that will be delivered by SMEs.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128320"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843915","Cabinet Office","false","2018-02-26","<p>Each contract has its own risk profile and government has always worked to reduce risk.</p><p>Government contracts are never awarded lightly: each contract is awarded following a transparent and robust process. Government fully complies with procurement regulations and follows these diligently when advertising and awarding contracts, including assessing suppliers’ suitability.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843915/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-26T17:09:10.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843915/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843915/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-19","Government Departments: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps his Department takes to assess supply chain risks in government procurement.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128321"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843916","Cabinet Office","false","2018-02-26","<p>We expect suppliers to mitigate appropriately against any real or perceived conflict of interest through their work with government. A supplier with a position of influence gained through a contract should not use that position to unfairly disadvantage any other supplier or reduce the potential for future competition, for example by creating a technical solution that locks in the supplier’s own goods or services.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843916/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-26T17:07:18.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843916/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843916/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-19","Government Departments: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps his Department takes to assess potential conflicts of interest between suppliers in government procurement.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128031"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843917","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-21","<p>Suppliers should be open and transparent with government in relation to breaches or suspected breaches of this Supplier Code of Conduct and should promptly notify government of any such breach. If non-compliance with the requirements of this code is reported or alleged, the first step is for government to discuss it with the supplier. If that does not result in a return to compliance, or in cases where the breach is sufficiently grave, government will look towards the eight principles of Corporate Renewal, as outlined in the National Audit Office report published in September 2014 on “Transforming government’s contract management” to rectify the breach.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843917/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-03-21T14:30:38.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843917/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843917/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-19","Government Departments: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps his Department takes to assess compliance with the supplier code of conduct.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128032"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843918","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-27","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>The information is not held in the requested format. NHS Business Services Authority does not hold data relating to the dosage or the time period for which drugs are prescribed.</p><p> </p><p>Provided in the table below are the number of unique patients who have been prescribed benzodiazepines and z-drugs during the last full two years for which data is available.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Period</p></td><td><p>Drug Group</p></td><td><p>Number of unique identifiable patients</p></td><td><p>Proportion of Items where patient could be identified</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January 2016 - December 2016</p></td><td><p>Benzodiazepine</p></td><td><p>1,631,587</p></td><td><p>93.22%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January 2017 - December 2017</p></td><td><p>Benzodiazepine</p></td><td><p>1,605,565</p></td><td><p>94.60%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January 2016 - December 2016</p></td><td><p>Z-Drug</p></td><td><p>1,039,141</p></td><td><p>95.19%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January 2017 - December 2017</p></td><td><p>Z-Drug</p></td><td><p>1,012,079</p></td><td><p>96.33%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843918/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T16:49:58.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843918/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843918/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Prescription Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the Answer of 21 December 2017 to Question 119603 on prescription drugs, what information his Department holds on the number of unique patients prescribed (a) benzodiazepines and (b) z drugs, including the duration of those prescriptions, for the last full two years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","128033"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843919","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-27","<p>The information is not held in the requested format. NHS Business Services Authority does not hold data relating to the dosage or the time period for which drugs are prescribed.</p><p> </p><p>Provided in the table below are the number of unique patients who have been prescribed anti-depressants and opioids for the last full two years for which data is available.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Period</p></td><td><p>Drug Group</p></td><td><p>Number of unique identifiable patients</p></td><td><p>Proportion of Items where patient could be identified</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January 2016 - December 2016</p></td><td><p>Antidepressants</p></td><td><p>7,038,347</p></td><td><p>96.27%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January 2017 - December 2017</p></td><td><p>Antidepressants</p></td><td><p>7,252,924</p></td><td><p>97.33%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January 2016 - December 2016</p></td><td><p>Opioids</p></td><td><p>3,156,156</p></td><td><p>94.04%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January 2017 - December 2017</p></td><td><p>Opioids</p></td><td><p>3,131,472</p></td><td><p>95.10%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843919/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T16:51:06.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843919/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843919/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Prescription Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what information his Department holds on the number of unique patients who have been prescribed (a) anti-depressants and (b) opioids, including the duration of those prescription in each of the last full two years for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","128035"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843920","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-27","<p>The information requested is given in the following table.</p><p> </p><p>The number of finished admission episodes (FAEs) with a primary diagnosis of drug-related mental and behavioural disorders for the years 2014-15 to 2016-17.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Primary diagnosis</p></td><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>2016-17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mental and behavioural disorders due to use of alcohol</p></td><td><p>45,297</p></td><td><p>44,491</p></td><td><p>40,428</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mental and behavioural disorders due to use of opioids</p></td><td><p>1,962</p></td><td><p>1,642</p></td><td><p>1,430</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mental and behavioural disorders due to use of cannabinoids</p></td><td><p>1,312</p></td><td><p>1,606</p></td><td><p>1,301</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mental and behavioural disorders due to use of sedatives or hypnotics</p></td><td><p>234</p></td><td><p>233</p></td><td><p>222</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mental and behavioural disorders due to use of cocaine</p></td><td><p>511</p></td><td><p>643</p></td><td><p>692</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mental and behavioural disorders due to use of other stimulants, including caffeine</p></td><td><p>974</p></td><td><p>916</p></td><td><p>660</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mental and behavioural disorders due to use of hallucinogens</p></td><td><p>138</p></td><td><p>186</p></td><td><p>153</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mental and behavioural disorders due to use of tobacco</p></td><td><p>510</p></td><td><p>431</p></td><td><p>762</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mental and behavioural disorders due to use of volatile solvents</p></td><td><p>24</p></td><td><p>31</p></td><td><p>13</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mental and behavioural disorders due to multiple drug use and use of other psychoactive substances</p></td><td><p>3,331</p></td><td><p>3,817</p></td><td><p>3,501</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>54,293</p></td><td><p>53,996</p></td><td><p>49,162</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: Hospital Episode Statistics, NHS Digital</p><p> </p><p>Note:</p><p> </p><p>A FAE is the first period of inpatient care under one consultant within one healthcare provider.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843920/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T15:30:14.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843920/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843920/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Drugs: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many hospital admissions with a primary diagnosis of drug-related mental health or behavioural disorder there were by (a) drug and (b) group of drugs in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","128322"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843921","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-27","<p>Data collected by NHS Digital does not differentiate whether a substance has been taken illegally or has been prescribed. However data is collected on finished admission episodes (FAEs) with a primary diagnosis of poisoning and toxic effect for the financial years between 2014-15 and 2016-17. These figures are provided in the attached tables.</p><p>A FAE is the first period of inpatient care under one consultant within one healthcare provider. FAEs are counted against the year or month in which the admission episode finishes. Admissions do not represent the number of inpatients, as a person may have more than one admission within the period.</p><p> </p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843921/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T16:24:28.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843921/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843921/answer","Copy of PQ128037 KD.xlsx","Copy of PQ128037 KD.xlsx","Finished Admission Episodes Poisoning","Finished Admission Episodes Poisoning","17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Drugs: Misuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many hospital admissions with a primary diagnosis of poisoning by illicit drugs there were by (a) drug or (b) group of drugs in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","128037"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843922","Cabinet Office","false","2018-02-27","<p>We remain committed to making better use of data across government and opening up government data sets where appropriate. We have been developing plans for a Chief Data Officer role and more information will be announced in due course. In the meantime, the Chief Executive of the Civil Service will continue to chair the Data Advisory Board to drive forward this agenda at the most senior level in Government.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843922/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T11:15:13.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843922/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843922/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-02-19","Cabinet Office: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when the Government plans to appoint a Chief Data Officer.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","128323"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843923","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-22","<p>Up to 20% of women are affected by mental illness during pregnancy or within the first year after giving birth. This covers a wide range of conditions.</p><p> </p><p>This Government is committed to improving perinatal mental health services for women during pregnancy and in the first postnatal year, so that women are able to access the right care at the right time and close to home.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is investing £365 million from 2015/16 to 2020/21 in perinatal mental health services, and NHS England is leading a transformation programme to ensure that by 2020/21 at least 30,000 more women each year are able to access evidence-based specialist mental health care during the perinatal period. This includes access to psychological therapies and specialist community or inpatient care.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843923/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T11:32:09.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843923/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843923/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Postnatal Care: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what information his Department holds on the incidence of mental health problems identified during the postnatal period; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","128039"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843924","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-02-27","<p>My Department has regular discussions with the Royal Borough of Kensington and Chelsea on housing and other support services for those affected by the Grenfell Tower fire, including some who do not have settled immigration status. The Government will ensure that, subject to usual checks, all those who are required to either provide evidence in person, or to be in the UK to participate in the Grenfell Tower Inquiry will be allowed to do so.</p><p> </p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843924/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T17:39:43.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843924/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843924/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-02-19","Grenfell Tower: Fires","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what discussions he has held with Kensington and Chelsea Council on the provision of (a) housing and (b) other support services for individuals bereaved by the Grenfell Tower fire who do not have (i) settled immigration status in the UK and (ii) recourse to public funds but who are core participants in the Grenfell Inquiry.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","128324"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843925","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-02-27","<p>There has been no move from 50 metres to 20 metres.</p><p> </p><p>Disability Living Allowance (DLA) does not have and has never had a 50 metre measure for mobilising for the purpose of assessing whether someone is unable or virtually unable to walk.</p><p> </p><p>The 20 metre distance was introduced in Personal Independence Payment (PIP) to distinguish those whose mobility is significantly more limited than others and who face even greater barriers on a day to day basis – those who have the highest need.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843925/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-27T15:59:20.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843925/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843925/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-02-19","Personal Independence Payment: Eligibility","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the evidential basis was for the decision to move personal independent payment mobility criteria from 50 metres to 20 metres.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","128040"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843926","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-02-22","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) is responsible for making decisions on the clinical and cost effectiveness of treatments. These can be very difficult decisions, and are made on the basis of very careful consideration of the evidence and public consultation. After considering the feedback from its consultation, NICE issued guidance in July 2016 which did not recommend Orkambi to treat cystic fibrosis. The decision was based on the evidence and price proposal provided by Vertex at the time of the appraisal.</p><p> </p><p>The guidance will be reviewed again in 2019. This review can be brought forward where there is new evidence that is likely to impact on the current recommendations, or if the company puts forward a proposal that demonstrates their drug is cost-effective.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843926/answer",,,,,,,,,,,,"2018-02-22T14:08:40.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843926/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/843926/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-19","Orkambi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what recent assessment his Department has made of the potential effect on patients with cystic fibrosis of making Orkambi available on the NHS; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","128042"
